So let me summarize: when the Left loses Existentialism it becomes trapped in Meaning, but Meaning does not survive The Singularity.
What this buys is a conceptual socialism which outcompetes capitalism at high rates of change because it has more bandwidth than just price.
Remember, the key to the Existential Left is that *they act without purpose* because purpose is derived from Meaning, and there is none.
The Mammonists are quite right, that a Planned Left cannot cope with challenges that The Market overcomes rapidly and easily these days.
So back to the Existential Left vs. the Mammonists. A Left based on inspired action (not resource allocation) vs. Capitalist Machines, say.
Today humans fight for stock options. Tomorrow AIs haggle over esoteric information-derivatives. All the same to Mammonists, really. Bingo.
But the Mammonists have a simple path forwards: individuals try to gain MORE, and what that looks like changes over time incl Singularity.
The worship of the Market is, of course, Mammonism. It's the worship of the demon of accumulation, and is our Established (State) Religion.
Now consider the Apocalyptic Right vs. the Old Left. They want to tear the government to pieces to make room for the Market. RIGHT NOW.
But deprived of a functional existential base, the increase in fundamental uncertainty increasingly reduces the Left to # paralysis # shambles
Yes, there is no purpose and no certainty, but I will feed these people because it is my will they do not suffer today *is enough* to work.
Leftism without meaning requires an embrace of the existential void, followed by a decision not to turn a blind eye to what we can see here.
In this respect the argument parallels Mahayana Buddhism in which action is taken to relieve suffering *for the benefit of the one doing it*
What I am basically suggesting is that the Singularity breaks meaning, and non-existential Left positions must generate meaning to exist.
You can't optimize a system no-one understands. What basis then is central planning going to have for making decisions? Singulartarian issue
This is the long lever that the Left lacks. In the face of Total Future Uncertainty, what is the basis for policy and planning these days?
Contrast Meaningless Solidarity with Teleological Solidarity. Action improvised in this hell vs HISTORICAL INEVITABILITY as a basis for life
Now, what do I mean by Meaningless Solidarity. Well, everything is infinite and pointless, and we can prove this. Now what do we do?
So let's pretend that Sartre kicks out Stalin and sides with Camus. Now we have a Socialism based in *meaningless* Solidarity. Yes. Really.
So the tragedy is that Sartre sides with Stalin. (roughly) Because that's where we lose a credible Existential Left. Which *can* do Change.
And this is why Stalinism can't cope with the Singularity (or for that matter any time of rapid chance.) You can't minimax such uncertainty.
The paralysis: if we start killing people to make more equal resource allocation how do we know we're killing a minimum number? Utilitarian!
And this uncertainty - Socialism Up An Exponential Curve - has produced a pervasive paralysis because it breaks Utilitarian world responses
Let me explain. On a limited resource base, you divide evenly and kill those who object. On a growing resource base YOU FREEZE AND WAIT.
And there's nothing in Socialism without Existentialism which can continue to take action in a Singularitarian environment. # paralysis
Because this is "static frame Marxism." with these resources how many thieves and kings must we kill to leave enough food for the survivors?

Now let's go back to Stalin. The modern left has not escaped Stalin, because to really root out the Stalinists would have destroyed it all.
